[b]SMC Structure & Expectation[/b] is a four-layer Smart Money Concepts indicator that works from raw swing structure up to confirmed entry setups — each layer only activating when the previous one is satisfied.

[b]What it does[/b]

Rather than firing signals directly from oscillators or crossovers, the indicator builds context bottom-up: first it establishes objective structure, then derives a logical expectation from that structure, then confirms with Break of Structure and Order Blocks. The result is a setup that requires multiple conditions to align before anything appears on the chart.

[b]Layers[/b]

[list]
[*][b]Swing Structure[/b] — Objective HH/HL/LH/LL detection; no predictions, only description of what price has actually done
[*][b]Expectation/Bias[/b] — Logical continuation derived from the structure sequence ("Expect HL", "Expect LH", "Continuation", "Failure")
[*][b]BOS + Order Blocks[/b] — Break of Structure confirmation with professional Order Block detection: displacement threshold (1.2 ATR), premium/discount location filtering, time-to-live, and mitigation tracking
[*][b]Warning Layer[/b] — Optional early signals for trendline breaks and potential top/bottom conditions; designed to minimize noise
[/list]

[b]Design philosophy[/b]

Each layer acts as a filter for the next. Order Blocks only form after a qualifying BOS. Bias only updates after a valid structural move. This reduces the number of signals but increases the quality of those that appear.

